Fionna (Flac IntO Normal/Native Audio). 

Fionna is audio converter for people who have a personal music library in open-source lossless audio codec and needs to have some music in MP3 for:
    portable player
    usb flash stick to use in car radio with usb
    etc.

Fionna is minimalistic and very easy-to-use. It lets you to copy a lot of flac tracks directly to mp3 with same filenames to given disk or path WITH NO any MP3 in your collection!

# changelog 

0.1 init release 

Commadn lines options are not supported yet (planned for 0.2). 

Planned command lines options are: 
	-p --path - output path for mp3 files
	-l --last - use mount point of  last mounted block device as a path
	-v --version - show current version
	-n --no-sort - don't sort partition (it will be sorted by default if fatsort installed)
	

Options and features planned fot 0.3:
	-s --split - split given flac image to to flac tracks using given CUE file
	-i --image - path to image
	-c --cue - path to CUE

I hope you will engoy it. See you soon. 
